\begin{align*}
0.72\overline{6}&=\frac{72}{100}+\frac{x}{10^{2}},\\
&=\frac{72}{100}+\frac{6x}{100},\\
&=\frac{72+6x}{100}.
\end{align*}
Now, since the decimal expansion ends, we have
\begin{align*}
72+6x&=72+0.6=\frac{72+0.6}{1}=\frac{73}{1},\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x&=\frac{73-72}{1}=\frac{1}{1}=\boxed{1}.
\end{align*}
So the final answer is $\boxed{72\frac{1}{10}}.$
